# Nava project rules

- **Git**: Commit after each logical change. Do not batch unrelated edits into one commit.
- **PROJECT_STATUS.md**: Update when adding features or completing work.
- **Supabase**: Add migrations to `supabase/migrations/`. Run `supabase db push` when adding/changing migrations or when saving/committing everything. Edge function secrets: `FROM_EMAIL`, `APP_URL`, `RESEND_API_KEY`, etc. — set via `supabase secrets set` or Dashboard.
- **Domain & email**: `vicomnava.com` verified with Resend. Emails send from `noreply@vicomnava.com`. Supabase secrets `FROM_EMAIL` and `APP_URL` must be set.
- **Desktop releases (Tauri)**: Use `npm run release -- <version>`. Signing key at `~/.tauri/nava.key` — never commit. GitHub Secrets `TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY` and `TAURI_SIGNING_PRIVATE_KEY_PASSWORD` enable CI signed builds. Upload artifacts + `latest.json` to GitHub Release.
- **Components**: Break code into small, reusable components with imports. Avoid large monolith files.
